I"¿<p>NGC 4565, the Needle Galaxy, is one of the most prominent and famous edge-on spiral galaxies in the sky.</p>

<p>You can easily see the central hub and the large dust lane that cuts across the nucleus of the galaxy.  It blocks and reddens the light from the interior.  It is located about 30-50 million light years away from us.</p>

